3.85/5  rDev -12.7%look: 3.5 | smell: 3.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 42005 edition, 2 oz sample shared with HimerMan.
Pours a syrupy thick deep ruby red with hints of orange. Little to know carbonation, hence no head or lace. 
Aromas of alcohol are immediately evident. Behind that, maple syrup comes through and is quite intense. The aroma is unlike any other beer that I have ever smelled. As it continues to open up I get nice vanilla notes.
The tastes begin with sugary sweetness of maple syrup along with a hint of candied/dark caramelized sugars. The high alcohol content is evident from the second the beer hits the tongue. Sweet vanilla and thick sappy maple syrup flavors are prevalent throughout.
The mouthfeel is the epitome of full bodied with zero to mild carbonation. Finish is slightly dry due to the high alcohol but the sweetness and syrupy flavors leave a slick feeling on the palate long after you sip/savor.
Overall, I am glad I was able to sample this beer. It is excellent as a novelty beer, but is is really not beer at this ABV in my opinion. More like an aperitif or a desert wine. Too sweet and boost overall to be enjoyed often or even a few times a year to be honest and boost overall. Recommended definitely tontry once in your beer lifetime and to say that you tried it, but not something I need to revisit anytime soon. 1,285 charactersclaspada, Nov 19, 2011
